                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/8–2245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-22T08:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 22, 1945—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 22—6:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3001. I reported my conversation with Molotov in a message to the Secretary via
                    Navy channels August 14<note n="28a" xml:id="d695fn28a">Telegram No. 141845,
                            <ref target="#pg_973">p. 973</ref>.</note> in which Molotov stated that
                    Stalin did not now consider, for the reasons given in my message, <pb
                        facs="0989" n="979" xml:id="pg_979"/> that there was any need for the Soviet
                    Government to give written confirmation of his verbal assurances to support the
                    Open Door policy, and I requested instructions. As I received no reply to this
                    message, I telegraphed again yesterday<note n="29" xml:id="d695fn29">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> via Navy channel asking what decision
                    had been reached. I have had no further discussions with Molotov on this
                    subject.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
